The message counter is used to detect situations where the transmitting ECU malfunction repeats thesame frame all the time. The receiver of the formation may use the counter parameter to detect thissituation. The transmitting device will increase the message counter in every cycle. The message counterwill count from 0 to 7 and then wrap. The values 0x8 thru 0xE are SAE reserved and should be ignoredby the receiver.Value 0xF (all bits set to 1) will indicate that the message counter is not available. Forcompatibility purposes, TSC1 should also be honored if the message counter is not available from thetransmitting device.

State signal which indicates that the ABS is active. The signal is set active when wheel brake pressure actually starts to bemodulated by ABS and is reset to passive when all wheels are in a stable condition for a certain time. The signal can also be setactive when driven wheels are in high slip (e.g., caused by retarder). Whenever the ABS system is not fully operational (due to adefect or during off-road ABS operation) , this signal is only valid for that part of the system that is still working. When ABS isswitched off completely, the flag is set to passive regardless of the current wheel slip conditions.

Signal which indicates whether an ABS system is fully operational or whether its functionality is reduced by a defect or by anintended action (e.g., by activation of an ABS-off-road switch or during special diagnostic procedures). There are cases where thesignal is necessary to fulfill legal regulations for special applications (e.g., switching off integrated retarders).
Switch signal which indicates the position of the ABS off-road switch.
This parameter commands the ABS/EBS amber/yellow optical warning signal
State signal which indicates that ASR brake control is active. Active means that ASR actually controls wheel brake pressure atone or more wheels of the driven axle(s).

State signal which indicates that ASR engine control has been commanded to be active. Active means that ASR actually tries tocontrol the engine. This state signal is independent of other control commands to the engine (e.g., from the transmission) whichmay have higher priority.
Switch signal which indicates the position of the ASR 'hill holder' switch.
Switch signal which indicates the position of the ABS off-road switch.

The brake system may temporarily or generally limit the maximum brake performance available for external systems. A temporary limit may be nessary due to high brake temperature; a general limit may be defined by the vehicle manufacturer, e.g. a value of -2.5 m/s? due to liability reasons. The actual limit is communicated to the external systems that request braking. The limit is only effective in the XBR Priorities 01b to 11b. It is specified as an absolute acceleration in reference to the road.

Indicates the sender’s desire to abort an Eng start. This signal is used by Reqers and consenters toReq that the arbitrator cancel an Eng start that is in progress.

Indicates the sender’s desire to start the Eng. The Eng start arbitrator latches this signal and, ifpossible, completes the Eng start regardless of a change of Sts of this signal. Use Eng Start AbortReq (SPN 7747) to un-latch the start Req and cancel an Eng start that is in progress.

Checksum to allow detection of data integrity issues. The receiving node shall calculate the checksum andcompare its calculated value with the received checksum. In case of a mismatch the message shall bediscarded.The message checksum is calculated using the first 7 data bytes, including the message counter, and thebytes of the message identifier. It is calculated as follows:Checksum = (Byte1 + Byte2 + Byte3 + Byte4 + Byte5 + Byte6 + Byte7 + message ID low byte +message ID mid low byte + message ID mid high byte + message ID high byte)

Message counter to allow detection of data integrity issues. The counter is incremented every time adevice sends out the Eng Start Ctrl message. When the counter has reached a value of 15 it startsover at 0 for the next message cycle. Receiving devices shall treat the message content as invalid whentwo consecutive messages from the same source address contain non-sequential counter values.

系统状态
0000  undefined 未定义（客户无需接入）
0001  Nmwait（int）未唤醒时的状态，等待网络唤醒。此时未上15电。
0010  terminal30wait 未使用，客户无需接入
0011  predrive 上15电自检过程
0100  drivedown 15电上电完成，自检完成无错误，CAN网络正常，发动机未起动
0101  driveup 发动机起动完成，无错误
0110  postrun 下电过程中
0111  off 下电完成进入OFF
1000  error 错误
1001  flash 刷写时进入的状态，本项目不用
1010  lowvolt 低压状态，本项目不用
1110  ERR 信号错误
1111  SNA 信号不可用

外部控制功能状态。
0x0:外部控制关闭，上电默认进入此状态
0x1:外部控制功能开启，进入等待状态，来自上层控制的反馈
0x2:外部控制功能中的手力矩控制模式，来自上层控制的反馈
0x3:外部控制功能中的电机扭矩控制模式，来自上层控制的反馈
0x4:外部控制功能中的方向盘转角控制模式，来自上层控制的反馈
0x5:外部控制功能中的取消控制，来自上层控制的反馈
0x6:外部控制被锁，表示进入严重错误，当前驾驶循环内无法再响应外部控制命令，相当于ERROR。此状态客户无需发送。

外部控制模式选择
0x0:关闭状态，上电时需要上位机发送此状态
0x1:待机状态，进入外部控制的初始状态。如果需要外部控制，需要上位机首先发送此状态。正常退出外部控制时，需要上位机发此值，让转向机保持ready状态。进行控制模式（手力控制-电机扭矩控制-转角控制）切换时，首先应发送ready使转向机进入ready，然后再发送目标控制模式命令要求转向机进入目标控制模式。
0x2:驾驶员手力矩控制模式，此模式下响应FBFTorqueReq
0x3:电机扭矩控制模式，此模式下响应MotorTorqueReq
0x4:转向角度控制模式，此模式下响应StrgAngleReq
0x5:客户可以发送此命令取消外部控制。一旦外部控制进入取消，上位机需要发送'OFF'→“READY' 来重新进入外部控制。
0x6:外部控制功能锁止，本项目不适用。本项目锁止状态为转向机内部自行判断进入，不响应外部控制信号进入。

The XBR Priority is used as an input to the Brk Sys to manage the priority of overlapping external and internal Reqs.
The XBR Ctrl Mode is used as an input to the Brk Sys and defines how the external Acc demand has to berealized.
The XBR EBI (Endurance Brk Integration) Mode is used as an input for the Brk Sys to prescribe the use of enduranceBrks like retarders or Eng Brks.

Parameter provided to the Brk Sys from external sources. This is the Acc which the Brk Sys is expected torealize. It is specified as an absolute Acc in reference to the road. Pstv values lead to increasing Vhcl speed,Ngtv values lead to decreasing Vhcl speed.Note: Normally only the Ngtv data range is used,but e.g. in case of downhilldriving also Pstv values are possible.
